caption: It took me right back to my time in Antigua, Guatemala. The handmade corn tortillas are delicious and the soups warm the body and the soul. La Bamba is a true gem of Silver Spring.
Try the tamales! The best Guatemalan tamales.

La Bamba is a hidden gem in downtown Silver Spring. I ate here for lunch a few weeks ago and I loved it! The pupusas are so good! I also tried their shrimp and rice in white wine sauce; I had to take it home because the portions are huge. Equally satisfying! I was there for lunch during the week, so I could only try one drink, but the sangria did not disappoint! I definitely want to come back and try more of their menu/drink options. This is a cute little family-style restaurant. My waitress was really nice, I highly recommend!

Very lovely experience here at this restaurant! Service was good, as well as quick.  It was our first time enjoying some of these Guatemalan foods - such as the chuchito and rellenito. Enjoyed both of those a lot, especially the chuchito, which is very similar to (or even another form of) a tamale if I had to compare. The salsa that comes out with complimentary chips is wonderful - very fresh.  One downside - we really didn’t care for the ceviche to be honest. I believe called coctel de camaron (though I may have butchered that a bit). The shrimp were a bit dry/overcooked, and I generally don’t care for ceviche when it has a tomato base.  Otherwise, we had a really nice experience here. All of the servers speak Spanish, so we also got to practice our Spanish skills, which was a fun challenge. If you’re looking for good food and an authentic cultural experience to branch out of your comfort zone, this is your place.  #lasamba #chuchito #rellenito #guatamalanfood #comidadeguatemala

Don't dismiss this place as just another authentic Mexican joint based on the name. It's a great authentic Guatemalan restaurant with a unique menu. Had the Picante de Pollo entree which was stellar and aggressively spicy. The chicken tamales we had for appetizers were the best tamales I've had in a long time. Highly recommended.
